The paper presents an algorithmic approach to the Temp Secretary Problem and its extensions, which involves designing online algorithms with improved performance guarantees. This falls under the category of algorithm design and analysis, which is covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also involves analyzing the competitive ratios of the algorithms, which is related to the field of online learning and prediction, covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves generalizing the problem to include packing constraints and arbitrary hiring durations, which involves optimization and decision-making, covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
